    x1). With the normalization ui1 = 0, this approximation can be reduced to (ui3/ui2)[(x2 – x1)/(x3 – x2)] – (x3 –
    x1)/(x3 – x2). As the fractions involving differences in the x’s are constant across subjects, it follows that the
    ratio ui3/ui2 summarizes the relevant information on agent i’s aversion to risk.

